.TH "acpi_node_get_gpiod" 9 "acpi_node_get_gpiod" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
acpi_node_get_gpiod \- get a GPIO descriptor from ACPI resources
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct gpio_desc *" acpi_node_get_gpiod
.BI "(struct fwnode_handle *fwnode "  ","
.BI "const char *propname "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "struct acpi_gpio_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fwnode" 12
pointer to an ACPI firmware node to get the GPIO information from
.IP "propname" 12
Property name of the GPIO
.IP "index" 12
index of GpioIo/GpioInt resource (starting from 0)
.IP "info" 12
info pointer to fill in (optional)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If \fIfwnode\fP is an ACPI device object, call \fBacpi_get_gpiod_by_index\fP for it.
Otherwise (i.e. it is a data-only non-device object), use the property-based
GPIO lookup to get to the GPIO resource with the relevant information and use
that to obtain the GPIO descriptor to return.

If the GPIO cannot be translated or there is an error an ERR_PTR is
returned.
